# Walkthrough: Account Limits Management and De-capping Contract

I have implemented the "Gestion Experte et Contrat de Déplafonnement" feature, allowing Administrators to manage account limits and generate formal printable contracts.

## Changes Made

### Backend Implementation
- **[PlafondModel.php](file:///c:/xampp/htdocs/ebanking/app/Models/PlafondModel.php)**: Created this model to manage the `plafonds_comptes` table. It handles fetching and updating limits for accounts.
- **[AdminController.php](file:///c:/xampp/htdocs/ebanking/app/Controllers/AdminController.php)**: 
    - Integrated the [PlafondModel](file:///c:/xampp/htdocs/ebanking/app/Models/PlafondModel.php#7-94).
    - Added [managePlafonds](file:///c:/xampp/htdocs/ebanking/app/Controllers/AdminController.php#284-295) to list all accounts and their current limits.
    - Added [editPlafond](file:///c:/xampp/htdocs/ebanking/app/Controllers/AdminController.php#296-319) and [updatePlafond](file:///c:/xampp/htdocs/ebanking/app/Controllers/AdminController.php#320-356) for modifying thresholds with strict validation and audit logging.
    - Added [contratPlafond](file:///c:/xampp/htdocs/ebanking/app/Controllers/AdminController.php#357-392) to generate a formal, printable contract, also logged for audit purposes.

### Frontend Implementation
- **[manage_plafonds.php](file:///c:/xampp/htdocs/ebanking/app/Views/admin/manage_plafonds.php)**: A new administrative dashboard to oversee all account limits with search functionality.
- **[edit_plafond.php](file:///c:/xampp/htdocs/ebanking/app/Views/admin/edit_plafond.php)**: A secure form geared towards modifying Daily Withdrawal, Daily Deposit, and Monthly Transfer limits.
- **[contrat_plafond.php](file:///c:/xampp/htdocs/ebanking/app/Views/admin/contrat_plafond.php)**: A professional, printable A4 document designed to hide all browser-specific print artifacts (URLs, dates) while maintaining a premium look.
- **[header.php](file:///c:/xampp/htdocs/ebanking/app/Views/layout/header.php)**: Integrated the new feature into the Admin sidebar under the label "Gestion Plafonds".

## Verification Results

### 1. Functional Testing
- **Access Control**: Verified that only accounts with `role_id = 1` (Admin) can access the management routes.
- **Limit Updates**: Successfully updated limits for an account and verified that the changes persisted in the database and were reflected in the UI.
- **Audit Logging**: Confirmed that every update (`PLAFOND_UPDATE`) and contract viewing (`CONTRAT_PLAFOND_VIEW`) is correctly recorded in the `Journal_Audit` table with the administrator's ID and relevant details.

### 2. Print Layout Verification
- **Browser Artifacts**: The specific CSS reset for `@media print` ensures that the URL, date, and page numbers are removed from the browser's default print signature.
- **Visual Excellence**: The contract layout includes a double-signature box, formal bank header, and clear identification of the account holder and new limits, meeting the "Paroxysme de qualité" requirement.

### 3. Error Handling
- **Invalid IDs**: Verified that attempting to edit a non-existent account redirects safely to the main list with a clear error message.
- **Data Validation**: Verified that negative values or invalid account references are rejected during the update process.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> To test the print layout, navigate to **Gestion Plafonds**, click **Contrat** for any account, and then click **IMPRIMER LE CONTRAT** (or Ctrl+P). The print preview should be clean and professional.
